  "lyrics": "*Music* Now you're registering So pretty little thing that drives me wild Is the same thing that drives me up Then guys wild and tall Well it'd be beautiful for us to keep a donut, no, it says what we do, a butterfly, deep fly, you can't You can't hear this, come to a lie that you want me to do What you do go on and fly with those wings baby it's true to you my baby I don't know it, it's the right way to go But if you let it go, and you said it for your little bit [Music] The verse to give somebody else a feeling that I feel But why should I be so? Pain capable of sharing *music* I can't describe the way it feels when you are alive Never would I want you to dream [Music] Oh, let me rephrase And the day I've never said mean about you, baby Beautiful way you are my butterfly [Music] (music) *I'm not a bad guy* We are feeling my butterfly, loyal, whenever it's tones and white lies in my butterfly. Don't you question! Fuck! She goes, please.",
  "lyricsSegments": [
